Job Description
Share
1.	Job Purpose:
Installs, overhauls, commissions, maintains and repair electrical, electronic, pneumatic, mechanical and analytical instrument and control systems used in Water, Power Generation, utility, Oil and Gas cluster. Guiding the Instrument Technician on their jobs and diagnosing faults.
(work covers all oil and gas cluster process areas on ZCSC including CSP, Flare system, oil riser and oil collection platform, Fuel Gas Systems, Service and Instrument Air System, Fire Water System, Sprinkler, System, Diesel Storage System, HVAC System, Workshop and Storage Facilities, CCR, Slops system, Salt Water, Fresh Water and Hot Water Systems, Sewage Treatment Plant, Emergency Generators, Laboratory Equipments, Gymnasium Equipments, Life Boat Instruments.)
2.	Principal Accountabilities:
•	Receives work assignments from supervisor and works either alone or with the assistance of fitters/helpers as required.
•	Installs, maintain and repair, electronic, pneumatic, mechanical and analytical instruments and controls systems on oil and gas cluster process plants. Work may be performed on site or in workshop as assigned by Instrument Supervisor (ZC).
•	Coordinates Supervisory on fault, required repair, required spares and general improvements to the system.
•	Trouble-shoots control related minor problems and report major problems and emergencies to instrument supervisor.
•	Maintains tools/test equipment in safe/reliable condition. Maintain good housekeeping.
•	Performs other duties as assigned such as taking part in training / developing new recruits/ UAE National employees/ develops.
•	Participates in Emergency team as assigned. Participate in Group safety meetings.
•	Ensures compliance with Company HSE regulations, procedures and standards.
•	 Work in line with HSE policy, and ensure awareness and compliance of HSE rules and regulations by subordinates.
Desired Candidate Profile
3.	Minimum Requirements[Knowledge Skills & Experience
•	Secondary Education followed by 2 years formal training leading to a diploma in electrical, electronic or instrumentation related to control systems.
•	5-6 years experience in the maintenance and repair of pneumatic and electronic instrumentation.
•	Good knowledge of spoken and written English.
